item.description:
Genre: Electronic
Style: Experimental, Synth-pop
Release Date: Sep 14, 2018
Label: Columbia - 19075833831
Source: WebDL 16/48 5.1 E-AC3
Bit rate: 1.024 kb/s

"Planet Jarre 5.1" is a part of the "Planet Jarre: 50 Years of Music" compilation album by French electronic musician and composer Jean-Michel Jarre, released on 14 September 2018 to commemorate Jarre's 50 years in the music business. All tracks have been hand-picked, remastered and retouched by Jarre himself.

Jean-Michel Jarre is a pioneer in the electronic, ambient and new-age genres. His first mainstream success was the 1976 album Oxygène. More albums were to follow, but his 1979 concert served as a blueprint for his future performances around the world. Several of his albums have been released to coincide with large-scale outdoor events, and he is now perhaps as well-known as a performer as he is as a musician.

Planet Jarre has become a nice overview of his extensive career. It contains songs or parts of almost all his albums.
The 4LP vinyl and 2CD+2MC box sets come with a download card to "enter the world of Jean-Michel Jarre in 5.1". The download contains the whole album as WAV files, a video introduction from Jean-Michel Jarre and 12 mp4 files with Dolby Digital Plus (Enhanced AC-3) audio tracks.

02. Equinoxe 2 (5:02)

09. Switched On Leon (with The Orb) (4:45)
10. Coachella Opening (4:00)
11. Souvenir Of China (4:02)
12. Zoolookologie (3:47)

Release Info
These tracks are part of the Vinyl Box Set of Planet Jarre. It contains a download card with a code to download the exclusive 5.1 content. The mp4 files contain a static backdrop and a 5.1 Dolby Digital Plus (E-AC3) track. I've muxed the audio track from the mp4 files to m4a with MP4Box and added a cover. The cover is created by merging the text from the backdrop with the cover from Planet Jarre.
